column4: I'm having trouble upgrading to 10.10. When I start the upgrade installer it goes through to the point where it "calculating changes" then i get this message. "An unresolvable problem occurred while calculating the upgrade:
E:Error, pkgProblemResolver::Resolve generated breaks, this may be caused by held packages.
* Upgrading to a pre-release version of Ubuntu
* Running the current pre-release version of Ubuntu
* Unofficial software packages not provided by Ubuntu
open synaptic and goto edit->fix broken packages
Still the same. could it be because its not an LTS release?
can you paste bin me the full error output
and synaptic repair broken packages didn't work? edit your sources.list and hash out anything not ubuntu
